@page "/components/data-display/avatar/accessibility"
@layout MainLayout
@using Sunfish.UIAdapters.Blazor.Components.Showcase

<PageTitle>Avatar / Accessibility · Sunfish Kitchen Sink</PageTitle>

<SunfishExamplePanel Title="Avatar / Accessibility"
                     Breadcrumb="@_breadcrumb"
                     GitHubUrl="https://github.com/ctwoodwa/Sunfish/blob/main/apps/kitchen-sink/Pages/Components/DataDisplay/Avatar/Accessibility/Demo.razor"
                     Sources="@GeneratedSources">

    <Narrative>
        <p>
            <code>SunfishAvatar</code> is purely decorative by default: it has no role, is not focusable,
            and does not capture keyboard events. The accessibility work happens around it — via the text
            associated with the image, or by making the avatar part of a focusable trigger (button, link)
            when it acts as a control.
        </p>
        <p>
            For image avatars, always supply <code>Alt</code>. If the avatar sits next to a visible name
            label, pass <code>Alt=""</code> so the image does not duplicate the name for screen-reader
            users. For initials avatars, the rendered text already appears in the accessibility tree. When
            the avatar acts as a menu trigger or profile link, wrap it in a <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> or
            anchor with <code>aria-label</code> describing the action, not the person.
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Keyboard</strong> — non-interactive avatars are skipped by Tab. Interactive avatars
            (button-wrapped) respond to Enter and Space via native button semantics.
        </p>
    </Narrative>

    <Example>
        <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:1.25rem;">
            <div class="demo-row" style="align-items:center; gap:0.75rem;">
                <SunfishAvatar Src="https://i.pravatar.cc/80?img=30" Alt="Alice Nguyen" />
                <span>Image avatar with descriptive <code>Alt</code> — screen readers announce the name.</span>
            </div>

            <div class="demo-row" style="align-items:center; gap:0.75rem;">
                <SunfishAvatar Src="https://i.pravatar.cc/80?img=31" Alt="" />
                <span><strong>Alice Nguyen</strong> — empty <code>Alt</code> avoids duplicating the visible name.</span>
            </div>

            <div class="demo-row" style="align-items:center; gap:0.75rem;">
                <SunfishAvatar Initials="AN" />
                <span>Initials avatar — the text content is exposed in the accessibility tree automatically.</span>
            </div>

            <div class="demo-row" style="align-items:center; gap:0.75rem;">
                <button type="button"
                        class="sf-avatar-trigger"
                        aria-label="Open profile menu for Alice Nguyen"
                        style="background:transparent;border:0;padding:0;cursor:pointer;border-radius:50%;">
                    <SunfishAvatar Initials="AN" Bordered="true" />
                </button>
                <span>Interactive avatar — real <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> with <code>aria-label</code> names the action.</span>
            </div>

            <dl style="font-size:0.875rem; max-width:640px;">
                <dt><strong>Alt</strong> on image avatars</dt>
                <dd>Descriptive when the avatar stands alone; empty <code>""</code> when a visible name is adjacent.</dd>
                <dt><strong>Initials</strong></dt>
                <dd>Rendered as text, so it is read by screen readers without any extra ARIA.</dd>
                <dt><strong>Interactive wrapping</strong></dt>
                <dd>Wrap in a <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> or anchor when the avatar is clickable; supply
                <code>aria-label</code> describing the action (e.g. "Open profile menu").</dd>
                <dt><strong>Keyboard</strong></dt>
                <dd>Non-interactive avatars: not focusable. Interactive: Enter and Space fire the wrapping
                button's click handler via native browser behavior.</dd>
            </dl>
        </div>
    </Example>

</SunfishExamplePanel>

@code {
    private static readonly string[] _breadcrumb =
        ["Components", "Data Display", "Avatar", "Accessibility"];
}
